The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, April 13, 2004 				 Hughes net rises 54% to Rs 21 cr
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, April 12: Hughes Software Systems (HSS) has recorded a 54 per cent jump in its net profit at Rs 21.2 crore for the quarter ended March 31. 																								The company had registered a net profit of Rs 13.8 crore for the same period last year. 																								HSS has posted a 104 per cent rise in its year-on-year net profit at Rs 77.4 crore for 2003-04, against Rs 37.9 crore in the previous year. The board has recommended a final dividend of 50 per cent for 2003-04, subject to shareholders approval. 																								The company has earned a total income of Rs 104.7 crore during the reporting quarter.																								This fiscal, Hughes will focus on improving its performance in the BPO segment, particularly the telecom and IT sectors. 																								Arun Kumar, president and managing director of HSS, said, Our quarterly and annual financial results crossed the Rs 100-crore sales figure. This is a significant milestone for us and we plan to take Hughes to the next level and improve our position in the market.																								Kumar refused to comment on the possible merger with NewsCorp. We do not wish to comment on market speculations. A team within the DirecTV Group is examining the core and non-core areas of business. Based on this, the final picture will emerge, said Kumar.																								HSS is a subsidiary of DirecTV, a leading player in global software outsourcing. HSS offers services to about 100 customers worldwide, in telecom infrastructure, communication service providers and business process outsourcing sectors.
